<!-- ══════════ CONTENT ══════════ -->
<div class="docs-container">

    <!-- ── 1. QUICK START ── -->
    <div class="doc-section" id="quick-start">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-num">1</div>
            <div class="section-title">Quick Start</div>
        </div>
        <p class="section-text">
            Become a Digimon Tamer in 3 simple steps. Everything happens on X (Twitter) &mdash;
            just mention <a href="https://x.com/digimononx" style="color:#ff6600;text-decoration:none;">@digimononx</a> and start playing.
        </p>

        <div class="step-flow">
            <div class="step-item">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <img src="/digimon/baby/Chibomon.gif" alt="" style="width:48px;height:48px;image-rendering:pixelated;margin-bottom:8px;filter:drop-shadow(0 0 6px rgba(0,204,255,0.3));">
                <div class="step-title">Mention Us</div>
                <div class="step-desc">
                    Tweet <code style="background:#1a2332;color:#ffcc00;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px;">@digimononx tame</code> to hatch your first Digi-Egg
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <img src="/digimon/child/Agumon.gif" alt="" style="width:48px;height:48px;image-rendering:pixelated;margin-bottom:8px;filter:drop-shadow(0 0 6px rgba(0,204,255,0.3));">
                <div class="step-title">Train & Feed</div>
                <div class="step-desc">
                    Use <code style="background:#1a2332;color:#ffcc00;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px;">feed</code> to give data to your Digimon and level up
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
                <div class="step-num">3</div>
                <img src="/digimon/adult/Growlmon.gif" alt="" style="width:48px;height:48px;image-rendering:pixelated;margin-bottom:8px;filter:drop-shadow(0 0 6px rgba(0,204,255,0.3));">
                <div class="step-title">Digivolve & Battle</div>
                <div class="step-desc">
                    Reach Lv.5 to <code style="background:#1a2332;color:#ffcc00;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px;">digivolve</code>, then <code style="background:#1a2332;color:#ffcc00;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px;">battle</code> other tamers
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card green">
            <div class="card-title">Important Rules</div>
            <div class="card-text">
                <strong>1 Digimon per Tamer</strong> &mdash; Each X account can tame one Digimon at a time.<br>
                <strong>Your Digimon starts at Baby stage</strong> &mdash; Feed and train it to digivolve into stronger forms.<br>
                <strong>All commands happen on X</strong> &mdash; Just reply to or mention <strong>@digimononx</strong> with a command.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 2. ALL COMMANDS ── -->
    <div class="doc-section" id="commands">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-num">2</div>
            <div class="section-title">Commands</div>
        </div>
        <p class="section-text">
            All commands work by mentioning <strong>@digimononx</strong> on X.
            The AI agent reads your tweet and responds with a card image.
        </p>

        <div class="cmd-block">
            <div class="cmd-header">
                <div class="cmd-name">tame</div>
                <span class="cmd-tag core">Core</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cmd-body">
                <strong>Hatch a Digi-Egg and get your first Digimon.</strong><br>
                A random Baby-stage Digimon will be assigned to you. You'll receive a tame card showing your new partner, its type, and evolution path.<br>
                <div class="cmd-example">@digimononx tame</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cmd-block">
            <div class="cmd-header">
                <div class="cmd-name">feed</div>
                <span class="cmd-tag core">Core</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cmd-body">
                <strong>Feed data to your Digimon to gain XP.</strong><br>
                Has a <strong>1-hour cooldown</strong> between feeds. Each feed gives XP and helps your Digimon grow toward digivolution.<br>
                <div class="cmd-example">@digimononx feed</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cmd-block">
            <div class="cmd-header">
                <div class="cmd-name">check</div>
                <span class="cmd-tag social">Info</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cmd-body">
                <strong>View your Digimon's full status.</strong><br>
                Shows name, type, level, stage, XP progress, stats (HP, ATK, DEF, SPD), win/loss record, and mood.<br>
                <div class="cmd-example">@digimononx check</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cmd-block">
            <div class="cmd-header">
                <div class="cmd-name">battle @user</div>
                <span class="cmd-tag combat">Combat</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cmd-body">
                <strong>Challenge another tamer's Digimon to battle.</strong><br>
                Battles are determined by <strong>level</strong>, <strong>type advantage</strong>, and some luck. The winner gains <strong>+25 XP</strong>.
                Battle results are shown as a narrative story &mdash; no HP numbers, just the action.<br>
                <div class="cmd-example">@digimononx battle @othertamer</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cmd-block">
            <div class="cmd-header">
                <div class="cmd-name">digivolve</div>
                <span class="cmd-tag core">Core</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cmd-body">
                <strong>Evolve your Digimon to the next stage.</strong><br>
                Requires <strong>Level 5+</strong>. Your Digimon transforms into a stronger form. Level resets to 1 after evolution, but the new form is far more powerful.
                Multiple evolution paths are possible &mdash; you might get a different form each time!<br>
                <div class="cmd-example">@digimononx digivolve</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cmd-block">
            <div class="cmd-header">
                <div class="cmd-name">activity</div>
                <span class="cmd-tag social">Social</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cmd-body">
                <strong>Have your Digimon do a fun activity.</strong><br>
                Your Digimon interacts with another tamer's Digimon for a mini social event. Earns some XP too.<br>
                <div class="cmd-example">@digimononx activity</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cmd-block">
            <div class="cmd-header">
                <div class="cmd-name">format device / release</div>
                <span class="cmd-tag combat">Danger</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cmd-body">
                <strong>Release your Digimon and start over.</strong><br>
                Permanently deletes your current Digimon so you can tame a new one. <strong>This cannot be undone.</strong><br>
                <div class="cmd-example">@digimononx format device</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cmd-block">
            <div class="cmd-header">
                <div class="cmd-name">help</div>
                <span class="cmd-tag social">Info</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cmd-body">
                <strong>Get a list of all available commands.</strong><br>
                <div class="cmd-example">@digimononx help</div>
            </div>
