            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card purple">
            <div class="card-title">What OpenClaw Does</div>
            <div class="card-text">
                <strong>Command Parsing:</strong> Understands natural language &mdash; you can say "I want to feed my Digimon" or just "feed", both work.<br>
                <strong>Battle Narratives:</strong> Generates unique battle stories for every fight &mdash; no two battles read the same.<br>
                <strong>Digimon Personality:</strong> Each Digimon has a generated personality that affects its reactions when fed, battled, or played with.<br>
                <strong>Smart Replies:</strong> The X agent responds contextually &mdash; it knows your Digimon's history, stage, and mood.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card purple">
            <div class="card-title">Architecture</div>
            <div class="card-text">
                <strong>AI Layer:</strong> OpenClaw inference engine for natural language understanding<br>
                <strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js + Express.js real-time server<br>
                <strong>Database:</strong> SQLite3 persistent storage with volume backup<br>
                <strong>Card Engine:</strong> Server-side canvas rendering for battle/status/tame cards<br>
                <strong>X Integration:</strong> Twitter API v2 with OAuth 1.0a for seamless social gameplay<br>
                <strong>Hosting:</strong> Railway cloud infrastructure with persistent volumes
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 8. FAQ ── -->
    <div class="doc-section" id="faq">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-num">8</div>
            <div class="section-title">FAQ</div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card orange">
            <div class="card-title">How many Digimon can I have?</div>
            <div class="card-text">
                <strong>1 Digimon per tamer.</strong> If you want a different Digimon, use <code>format device</code> to release your current one, then <code>tame</code> again.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card orange">
            <div class="card-title">How do I digivolve?</div>
            <div class="card-text">
                Feed and battle your Digimon until it reaches <strong>Level 5</strong>, then use the <code>digivolve</code> command. Your Digimon will evolve into a random form from its evolution tree.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card orange">
            <div class="card-title">Why did I lose a battle?</div>
            <div class="card-text">
                Battles consider <strong>level difference</strong> and <strong>type advantage</strong>. A lower-level Digimon fighting against a type that counters it will likely lose. Check the type chart above!
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card orange">
            <div class="card-title">Can I choose which Digimon I tame?</div>
            <div class="card-text">
                No &mdash; taming is random! You get a surprise Baby-stage Digimon. The fun is discovering what you get and watching it evolve.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card orange">
            <div class="card-title">How long does feeding cooldown last?</div>
            <div class="card-text">
                <strong>1 hour</strong> between feeds. Use this time to battle or do activities instead!
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card orange">
            <div class="card-title">What happens after my Digimon reaches Mega?</div>
            <div class="card-text">
                Mega is the final evolution stage. Your Digimon is at maximum power! Keep battling to climb the leaderboard and show off your strength.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

